00:48.381 --> 00:50.872
MALLORY: Hello, l'm here.

00:50.984 --> 00:53.418
Where is everybody?

00:55.155 --> 00:58.249
Amy? Ty?

01:02.062 --> 01:05.206
l can't believe they left without me.

01:06.366 --> 01:08.501
Well, l didn't even know they still existed.

01:08.601 --> 01:12.628
l mean, l figured a Mustang was just a car.

01:12.739 --> 01:15.508
Well, a herd of them came
too far down the mountain.

01:15.608 --> 01:18.311
A couple of them already got shot.

01:18.411 --> 01:20.621
Why would anybody do that?

01:20.713 --> 01:23.383
Cattle ranchers think
they're a waste of grass.

01:23.483 --> 01:25.652
My dad and Ray want to ship them
back up to the mountains,

01:25.752 --> 01:29.407
so at least they'll be safe for the winter.

01:32.792 --> 01:34.817
What are they doing?

01:34.928 --> 01:36.928
l don't know.

01:40.600 --> 01:43.970
We never let a horse go
until we've made absolutely certain...

01:44.070 --> 01:48.320
...that its temperament is suited
to its new owner.

01:48.875 --> 01:51.077
You said your daughter's 1 2 years old?

01:51.177 --> 01:54.874
l have at least one horse that might work.

01:54.981 --> 01:57.717
We have a 1 2-year-old neighbor,
and she's riding one of our horses...

01:57.817 --> 02:00.787
...that she's completely compatible with.

02:00.887 --> 02:04.090
Oh, yeah, Copper
is absolutely perfect for her.

02:04.190 --> 02:06.624
Calm, gentle, broken in.

02:06.726 --> 02:09.429
l'm sure we can match your daughter
up with one of our horses.

02:09.529 --> 02:11.064
LOU: We've just...
- Lou?

02:11.164 --> 02:15.897
Yes, yes, we can definitely work
something out.

02:16.269 --> 02:17.937
l'm on the phone.

02:18.037 --> 02:20.240
So, great, see you tomorrow, then.

02:20.340 --> 02:22.501
LOU: Perfect.

02:31.618 --> 02:33.658
Hey, check out that one.

02:34.220 --> 02:37.090
That's a stallion.
You see those markings?

02:37.190 --> 02:40.165
That's a classic Appaloosa Mustang.

02:40.793 --> 02:43.819
Hey. This is private property.

02:43.930 --> 02:48.334
We're just here to see the Mustangs.
ls Ray around? Or Tim Fleming?

02:48.434 --> 02:51.232
You see them? 'Cause l don't.

02:51.838 --> 02:53.706
Well, then, who are you, guys?

02:53.806 --> 02:57.003
l work for Ray.
Now get outta here.

02:59.279 --> 03:01.543
Whoa. Whoa. Whoa.

03:01.648 --> 03:03.049
Hey. Ty.

03:03.149 --> 03:05.413
You got a problem, man?

03:06.519 --> 03:06.986
Huh?

03:07.086 --> 03:09.126
Ty. No. Forget about it.

03:15.895 --> 03:18.125
Next time.

03:23.836 --> 03:26.639
You better pray there ain't no next time.

03:26.739 --> 03:28.374
Ty.

03:28.474 --> 03:30.474
Let's go.

03:30.610 --> 03:33.713
Yeah, Ty. Do what your
little girlfriend tells you.

03:33.813 --> 03:36.441
Please, Ty.

03:42.021 --> 03:43.456
Give me half a dozen.

03:43.556 --> 03:47.466
Make sure they got
some meat on them this time.

04:04.110 --> 04:06.772
♪ And at the break of day♪

04:06.879 --> 04:11.714
♪ You sank into your dream♪

04:11.818 --> 04:14.343
♪ You dreamer♪

04:15.355 --> 04:17.789
♪ You dreamer♪

04:19.692 --> 04:24.857
♪ You dreamer♪

04:29.836 --> 04:31.037
Hey, l know you don't take...

04:31.137 --> 04:32.338
...just anyone on, Nick.

04:32.438 --> 04:34.641
But l really need somebody...

04:34.741 --> 04:36.242
...with your reputation...

04:36.342 --> 04:37.343
...to push me and Red here...

04:37.443 --> 04:39.443
...to the next level.

04:40.213 --> 04:40.947
ls this the horse...

04:41.047 --> 04:42.015
...that was in the accident...

04:42.115 --> 04:44.640
...when Marion Fleming died?

04:44.751 --> 04:46.751
Yeah. Spartan.

04:47.820 --> 04:48.988
l've heard Amy's brought him...

04:49.088 --> 04:50.290
...a long way since then.

04:50.390 --> 04:54.130
Excuse me?
l thought this was about my horse.

04:55.194 --> 04:57.489
Hey, Ben, l'm doing this...

04:57.563 --> 04:59.599
...as a favor to your aunt.

04:59.699 --> 05:03.829
So lose the attitude, okay?

05:12.612 --> 05:14.612
Nick. What are...?

05:15.281 --> 05:16.849
l haven't seen you in ages.

05:16.949 --> 05:18.585
Yeah. l was thinking something...

05:18.685 --> 05:19.719
...along those lines...

05:19.819 --> 05:21.988
...when Lisa Stillman called me up...

05:22.088 --> 05:24.357
...and asked me to coach her nephew.

05:24.457 --> 05:27.620
Oh, lucky you.

05:28.294 --> 05:31.229
Yeah.

05:31.331 --> 05:33.891
l saw Spartan at a few shows.

05:34.000 --> 05:35.702
A year or so ago.

05:35.802 --> 05:36.936
Didn't matter who was riding him,

05:37.036 --> 05:38.605
he always took the fences nice and clean.

05:38.705 --> 05:40.540
That's a special talent.

05:40.640 --> 05:42.767
And l was thinking if...

05:42.875 --> 05:43.910
Well, if Amy's not interested...

05:44.010 --> 05:44.611
...in showing him,

05:44.711 --> 05:47.447
l know some people who'd pay good
money for an honest horse like that.

05:47.547 --> 05:50.744
Oh, Amy would never sell him.

05:50.850 --> 05:54.020
But, just out of curiosity,
how much money?

05:54.120 --> 05:56.556
Well, um, you know, that depends.

05:56.656 --> 05:59.626
The way l do business, it's not
just about buying and selling.

05:59.726 --> 06:02.962
lt's about establishing
a relationship, you know,

06:03.062 --> 06:06.293
not a one time deal,
something ongoing.

06:06.399 --> 06:09.596
Uh, that is an interesting approach.

06:11.504 --> 06:14.394
Do you want to have lunch with me?

06:14.841 --> 06:16.476
We can talk about it.

06:16.576 --> 06:20.741
l'm working with Ben tomorrow.
Maybe the next day?

06:20.913 --> 06:22.938
Yeah, l guess.

06:23.049 --> 06:25.049
Sure. Okay.

06:25.685 --> 06:27.685
Hey, Lou.

06:29.722 --> 06:31.491
Hey, Nick.

06:31.591 --> 06:34.260
Hope l'm not interrupting anything.

06:34.360 --> 06:37.261
No, no, l was just leaving.

06:37.363 --> 06:39.888
l'll see you later, Lou.

06:44.170 --> 06:44.871
[ Clears throat ]

06:44.971 --> 06:50.068
That was some, uh,
nice timing there, Mr. Cardinal.

06:50.410 --> 06:52.970
You didn't plan that, did you?

06:53.079 --> 06:55.547
Planned what?

06:57.083 --> 06:59.711
Unbelievable.

07:00.286 --> 07:02.188
You should be glad
you weren't there, Mallory.

07:02.288 --> 07:04.524
There were these creepy guys
with a livestock trailer.

07:04.624 --> 07:06.392
Ty almost got into a fight with one of them.

07:06.492 --> 07:07.794
No, l didn't.

07:07.894 --> 07:11.564
Mustangs? Creepy guys? Fist fights?
What makes me happy l didn't come?

07:11.664 --> 07:13.766
One of them said he worked for Ray.

07:13.866 --> 07:14.967
Mmmm, that figures.

07:15.067 --> 07:17.270
Ray's gonna keep them penned up
for a couple of days.

07:17.370 --> 07:21.341
So l can get the DNA tested,
see if they really are Mustangs.

07:21.441 --> 07:23.209
What else would they be?

07:23.309 --> 07:25.678
Well, they could be
domestic horses gone wild.

07:25.778 --> 07:27.847
But real Mustangs aren't just feral horses.

07:27.947 --> 07:30.116
Their bloodlines date all the way
back to the Conquistadors,

07:30.216 --> 07:31.351
and they were originally
brought to Alberta...

07:31.451 --> 07:35.021
...by the Blackfoot lndians in the 1 630s.

07:38.090 --> 07:42.000
What? l wrote an essay on them
in grade eleven.

07:42.395 --> 07:43.896
Well, that's why l'm gonna test them.

07:43.996 --> 07:45.865
lf they really are Mustangs,

07:45.965 --> 07:49.535
they're one step closer
to being a protected species.

07:49.635 --> 07:51.938
You should come, Jack.
l could use the help.

07:52.038 --> 07:54.163
Mind if l bring Ty along?

07:56.742 --> 07:59.734
l figure your dad's gonna be there,

07:59.846 --> 08:03.926
and l'm gonna need someone
to break up the fight.

08:05.518 --> 08:07.518
That was a joke.

08:09.222 --> 08:12.749
Wild horses couldn't keep me away.

08:14.794 --> 08:18.025
That was a joke too.

08:23.135 --> 08:25.938
Hey, Nick was asking about Spartan today.

08:26.038 --> 08:27.440
What about Spartan?

08:27.540 --> 08:29.208
l don't know if this is the right time,

08:29.308 --> 08:31.778
but l'd like to discuss the Copper situation.

08:31.878 --> 08:34.514
What are you talking about, Mallory?
There is no Copper situation.

08:34.614 --> 08:35.815
Anyway, he was saying...

08:35.914 --> 08:38.384
...he had some clients
who were seriously interested--...

08:38.484 --> 08:40.086
...lnterested in what? Buying him?

08:40.186 --> 08:42.450
Yes, actually.

08:42.554 --> 08:43.756
Well, l'm not selling.

08:43.856 --> 08:44.390
l know, Amy.

08:44.490 --> 08:48.361
l'm just saying that you should
really think about showing him.

08:48.461 --> 08:51.297
And when do you think l'll have time
for that? Hmm?

08:51.397 --> 08:56.327
l've got school, the other horses.
l have no time to train.

08:56.435 --> 08:58.435
All right, whatever.

08:59.171 --> 09:01.662
l should do my homework.

09:14.186 --> 09:16.279
l hate your sister.

09:16.389 --> 09:20.325
Sometimes l'm not so thrilled
with her either.

09:20.459 --> 09:23.296
The Fall Finale Entry?
l thought you were doing homework.

09:23.396 --> 09:26.763
l was working on homework, Mallory.

09:27.199 --> 09:30.136
So, did Lou say anything to you
about Copper?

09:30.236 --> 09:31.637
Why would she?

09:31.737 --> 09:34.006
So the word re-homing never came up?

09:34.106 --> 09:36.042
No one is re-homing Copper, okay?

09:36.142 --> 09:38.010
Lou never said anything to me
about it, not once.

09:38.110 --> 09:39.779
She never said anything to me either.

09:39.879 --> 09:45.518
You're just being paranoid. l've got
to do the night check on the horses.

09:45.618 --> 09:48.788
Why are you in my room? And
why are you wearing my bathrobe?

09:48.888 --> 09:51.390
Who's paranoid now?
l'm sleeping over.

09:51.490 --> 09:54.890
Don't worry.
My mom and dad said l could.

09:58.631 --> 10:01.000
l can't believe my grandpa's
actually going up to Ray's,

10:01.100 --> 10:03.035
after what happened with my dad last time.

10:03.135 --> 10:05.605
l guess the pull of wild horses
is stronger than any grudge...

10:05.705 --> 10:07.340
...he might be holding.

10:07.440 --> 10:10.843
Yeah, it's funny.
l, uh, l wrote that paper.

10:10.943 --> 10:13.479
'The Living Heritage of the West.'

10:13.579 --> 10:15.147
And l've lived here for most of my life,

10:15.247 --> 10:18.184
but l've never actually seen a Mustang.

10:18.284 --> 10:21.854
When l was a kid, my grandpa,
he swore me to secrecy,

10:21.954 --> 10:27.226
but he took me to his special place,
and, uh, l saw a whole herd.

10:27.326 --> 10:33.526
Oh, l'd like to see that. l mean,
l don't know, maybe one day.

10:34.433 --> 10:39.564
So. There is a part of you
that still likes horses?

10:40.039 --> 10:44.204
Don't tell anyone.
l have a reputation to protect.

10:46.178 --> 10:48.271
Have a good night.

10:48.381 --> 10:50.381
Good night.

10:52.551 --> 10:54.551
Hm...

10:56.689 --> 10:59.025
Everybody says Spartan used to be
a pretty good jumper.

10:59.125 --> 11:01.491
Used to be.

11:02.395 --> 11:04.864
l've seen the ribbons on your wall, Amy.

11:04.964 --> 11:07.939
But there's room for a couple more.

11:08.000 --> 11:11.704
You know, if it was just him and me,
l would be fine.

11:11.804 --> 11:14.602
But it's Lou, it's Nick.

11:14.707 --> 11:16.642
lt's everybody who knows
about the accident,

11:16.742 --> 11:19.939
who knows he's not just a horse,

11:20.446 --> 11:24.016
he's the horse my mom died trying to save.

11:25.117 --> 11:27.117
Yeah.

11:27.420 --> 11:29.755
l guess it's a lot harder to get
a horse over one of those jumps...

11:29.855 --> 11:33.085
...when he's carrying so much baggage.

11:33.125 --> 11:37.425
But if anyone can do it, you can.

11:52.278 --> 11:54.278
Yes.

11:58.217 --> 12:00.512
Can you put that up for me?

12:10.463 --> 12:12.463
Come on.

12:14.533 --> 12:15.368
l got it.

12:15.468 --> 12:19.097
No, don't bother.
l'm done for the day.

12:20.673 --> 12:22.608
Come on.
At least, one more try.

12:22.708 --> 12:24.210
TY: You gotta end on a good note, right?

12:24.310 --> 12:25.244
AMY: l've gotta go to school.

12:25.344 --> 12:28.780
Hey. Did you move my jumps?

12:28.914 --> 12:32.518
l look out my window, and l see
all my jumps have been moved.

12:32.618 --> 12:36.443
Well, if it's such a big deal,
move them back.

12:36.555 --> 12:39.530
Well, you heard her.
Move them back.

12:46.232 --> 12:47.933
l mean, talk about a wake up call.

12:48.033 --> 12:50.703
When l saw you were looking
at the entry form for the Fall Finale,

12:50.803 --> 12:52.304
l had an epiphany.

12:52.404 --> 12:55.396
l should enter Copper too.

12:55.508 --> 12:58.811
Well, Copper isn't really a jumping
horse, he's never been trained.

12:58.911 --> 13:03.549
And he's not my horse.
That's what you really mean, isn't it?

13:03.649 --> 13:05.484
Come on, we're gonna be late for the bus.

13:05.584 --> 13:06.485
lsn't Lou driving us?

13:06.585 --> 13:10.022
No, she's got some people
coming to look at horses.

13:10.122 --> 13:11.991
Which horses?

13:12.091 --> 13:14.641
Just give it a rest.
Get ready.

13:17.463 --> 13:18.931
Wait. What about your stuff?

13:19.031 --> 13:19.832
Where are you going?

13:19.932 --> 13:21.500
l'm not going to school.

13:21.600 --> 13:23.269
Why not?

13:23.369 --> 13:26.133
l'm taking a mental health day.

13:41.754 --> 13:43.255
Can l help you?

13:43.355 --> 13:45.458
l'm looking for Lou Fleming.

13:45.558 --> 13:47.359
Oh, is this Copper?

13:47.459 --> 13:48.694
How did you know that?

13:48.794 --> 13:51.174
Well, Lou told me about him.

13:51.197 --> 13:52.898
You know, l've got a daughter
just about your age,

13:52.998 --> 13:55.401
who would die for a horse like this.

13:55.501 --> 13:57.303
Well, she might have to.

13:57.403 --> 14:01.774
l mean, he's a very difficult horse.
Pig-headed. Bad-tempered.

14:01.874 --> 14:03.342
Basically, unridable.

14:03.442 --> 14:05.945
Well, he certainly seems
calm enough to me.

14:06.045 --> 14:07.246
Now maybe.

14:07.346 --> 14:09.181
l definitely wouldn't wanna be
in a stall with him...

14:09.281 --> 14:10.916
...when his meds wear off.

14:11.016 --> 14:11.851
Lou assured me--

14:11.951 --> 14:15.546
She's depressed.
She's desperate.

14:15.654 --> 14:18.023
l mean, so many horses,
so little time.

14:18.123 --> 14:20.693
And when a well-meaning horse lover
like you calls...

14:20.793 --> 14:24.029
Uh, you know, l think it's probably
better if l talked to her myself.

14:24.129 --> 14:29.465
She's not here. She's out of town.
On 'vacation'.

14:29.702 --> 14:31.702
Hm...

14:41.247 --> 14:43.482
You know, l gotta say, Jack,

14:43.582 --> 14:46.652
l kind of respect you,
coming up here to help Ray,

14:46.752 --> 14:47.853
with your history and everything.

14:47.953 --> 14:51.357
The only history l give a damn about
is those Mustangs.

14:51.457 --> 14:54.160
My plan -- and this'll be your plan too --...

14:54.260 --> 14:58.297
...is we're just gonna watch,
strictly as observers.

14:58.397 --> 15:00.397
l'm down with the plan.

15:00.733 --> 15:04.669
l'm down with you being down
with the plan.

15:04.770 --> 15:10.402
Not going to let your friend Tim
get my goat, not this time.

15:12.077 --> 15:14.712
Hey, Mallory, have you seen...?

15:16.649 --> 15:18.649
l can see you there.

15:20.819 --> 15:23.117
Have you seen Mrs. Wiley?

15:23.222 --> 15:24.690
Who?

15:24.790 --> 15:28.851
No. Oh, she left.

15:28.961 --> 15:30.029
What did you say to her?

15:30.129 --> 15:33.621
Nothing. Hardly nothing. Why?

15:36.568 --> 15:37.937
Aren't you supposed to be in school?

15:38.037 --> 15:41.974
All the important stuff's
already over. Recess, Gym, Art.

15:42.074 --> 15:45.474
Now all that's left is science and math.

15:45.477 --> 15:49.004
Mrs. Wiley? Hi. lt's Lou.

15:50.049 --> 15:53.052
Yeah, l'm sorry for the inconvenience.

15:53.152 --> 15:56.849
How about four o'clock this afternoon?

15:56.956 --> 15:59.591
Okay, thanks for your patience.

16:11.470 --> 16:14.273
We're gonna start by separating
the mares from the studs,

16:14.373 --> 16:17.773
then funnel them into the squeeze chute.

16:19.778 --> 16:21.714
Hey, what happened to the rest of them?

16:21.814 --> 16:23.983
The last time l was here,
there was a lot more.

16:24.083 --> 16:24.884
You sure about that?

16:24.984 --> 16:26.819
Yeah. There was an Appaloosa stallion.

16:26.919 --> 16:29.622
Amy said it looked just like a Mustang.

16:29.722 --> 16:32.758
Well, l'm betting
a lot of these horses are Mustangs.

16:32.858 --> 16:34.326
What do you think, Jack?

16:34.426 --> 16:36.792
The configuration's wrong.

16:36.895 --> 16:38.497
You gotta widen that alleyway there,

16:38.597 --> 16:41.467
or you're never going to get them in
without a fight.

16:41.567 --> 16:43.936
Well, that's the way Tim wanted it.

16:44.036 --> 16:45.871
There's your second problem right there.

16:45.971 --> 16:49.626
Tim Fleming
is basically a weekend wrangler.

16:51.510 --> 16:52.878
You got a cuttin' horse ready to go?

16:52.978 --> 16:54.413
Yes, l do.

16:54.513 --> 16:57.488
You still down with the plan, Jack?

17:04.823 --> 17:16.030
Peanut butter, crackers,
juice boxes, cell phone.

17:16.135 --> 17:20.333
Not that anyone cares enough
about me to call.

17:20.705 --> 17:24.403
Last but not least, toilet paper.

17:30.649 --> 17:36.986
lf Lou wants to re-home you,
she's gonna have to find you first.

17:38.357 --> 17:39.792
So, what can l tell you?

17:39.892 --> 17:42.528
Nick came to see Red,
and he was totally psyched.

17:42.628 --> 17:42.962
That's so awesome.

17:43.062 --> 17:45.597
l have to come watch you train.
lsn't that awesome, Amy?

17:45.697 --> 17:47.232
Totally.

17:47.332 --> 17:49.768
What's the matter with you?
Why are you being so negative?

17:49.868 --> 17:52.071
Ben getting coached by Nick is huge.

17:52.171 --> 17:57.165
Nick? Nick Harwell?
He only works with top level riders.

17:57.309 --> 18:00.005
That's why he's coaching Ben.

18:00.112 --> 18:01.580
Oh, it's about time.

18:01.680 --> 18:03.682
At the show last week you did so well,

18:03.782 --> 18:05.384
it's crazy you didn't get a ribbon.

18:05.484 --> 18:08.887
Yeah, l know. l mean, that last fence,
the rail wasn't even in the cup.

18:08.987 --> 18:10.422
Red barely touched it,
and it came down.

18:10.522 --> 18:12.725
The jump crew
was so obviously incompetent.

18:12.825 --> 18:14.660
l couldn't believe you didn't
complain to the judge.

18:14.760 --> 18:17.496
Yeah, well, that's why
l've gotta work with Nick.

18:17.596 --> 18:18.931
l mean, the guy's connected.

18:19.031 --> 18:21.066
Stuff like that doesn't happen to his people.

18:21.166 --> 18:23.602
Yeah, but, Ben, l mean,
no matter what you do,

18:23.702 --> 18:27.706
l'm still going to beat your ass
at the Fall Finale.

18:27.806 --> 18:32.072
Speaking of which, Amy,
l saw the entry list.

18:32.177 --> 18:33.545
l didn't see your name on it.

18:33.645 --> 18:35.914
l thought you'd be riding
that washed up show-jumper...

18:36.014 --> 18:38.384
...you've got sitting in your back field.

18:38.484 --> 18:40.886
Why don't you ask Nick
how washed up my horse is?

18:40.986 --> 18:43.876
He's the one who wants to buy him.

18:45.724 --> 18:50.525
But, hey, what does he know
about show jumping, right?

18:59.505 --> 19:04.265
Yeah, l'm telling you,
they've been down there for weeks.

19:04.610 --> 19:08.480
Yeah, we'll pick up another dozen
and get 'em all down to you tonight.

19:08.580 --> 19:10.580
All right.

19:18.023 --> 19:21.253
Going the wrong way there,
little girl.

19:22.561 --> 19:24.893
Come on.

19:41.513 --> 19:43.916
Jack Bartlett,
on one of my cuttin' horses.

19:44.016 --> 19:45.284
Never thought l'd see the day.

19:45.384 --> 19:47.886
l figured this had to be one of yours.

19:47.986 --> 19:49.955
You never did have much luck
picking horses.

19:50.055 --> 19:53.025
So, you came all the way up here
just to insult me?

19:53.125 --> 19:54.493
[ Laughs ]

19:54.593 --> 19:59.131
Well, the way l see it, it's a two-man
operation, so we'll work as a team.

19:59.231 --> 20:02.835
Oh, like the old days?
Yeah, so you're the boss?

20:02.935 --> 20:08.006
Got that right. And the intervening
years will be temporarily forgotten.

20:08.106 --> 20:12.478
l'll cut the horse from the herd,
you drive it down the chute.

20:12.578 --> 20:15.103
Okay, Jack.

20:21.687 --> 20:23.355
Aim for the middle.

20:23.455 --> 20:25.455
Nicely done.

20:26.625 --> 20:32.490
Support him with your inside leg,
so he doesn't fall in at the corner.

20:32.998 --> 20:34.998
Yeah, Ben.

20:35.968 --> 20:38.370
Since when did you become
a big show jumping fan?

20:38.470 --> 20:41.340
What? Just because l don't go on
and on about it like you do.

20:41.440 --> 20:43.465
Or since you met Nick?

20:43.575 --> 20:49.673
Oh, come on, Amy.
He's just like... bonus.

20:52.618 --> 20:56.247
Okay, let the horse catch his breath.

20:56.488 --> 21:01.126
Not bad, this kid. l'm surprised
he doesn't do better at competitions.

21:01.226 --> 21:03.028
What do you think, Amy?

21:03.128 --> 21:06.427
Um, l don't know, it could be nerves.

21:06.732 --> 21:08.433
You don't sound convinced.

21:08.533 --> 21:11.837
What's the deal, Amy? You've
seen him ride a million times.

21:11.937 --> 21:17.204
Yeah. Without moving the jumps
or changing the course.

21:22.080 --> 21:23.549
Hey, Ben.

21:23.649 --> 21:24.349
Yeah?

21:24.449 --> 21:26.118
We're gonna reverse the course.

21:26.218 --> 21:30.989
Want you to pop over these
two fences, going away from home.

21:31.089 --> 21:33.887
Uh, that way?

21:33.992 --> 21:35.427
l don't get it.
What's the point?

21:35.527 --> 21:38.332
Just gonna shake things up a bit.

21:38.563 --> 21:40.563
All right.

21:51.109 --> 21:53.109
He took off too early.

21:55.647 --> 21:58.707
That time, he went too deep.

21:59.184 --> 22:01.954
Your sister's right.
He can't see a distance.

22:02.054 --> 22:04.790
lf he doesn't learn that,
he's got no real future as a jumper.

22:04.890 --> 22:06.325
Are you talking about Red?

22:06.425 --> 22:09.485
No. That horse is fine.

22:09.594 --> 22:11.594
l'm talking about Ben.

22:18.403 --> 22:21.566
Okay, here they come.

22:27.746 --> 22:29.746
Come on.

22:30.015 --> 22:32.015
Come on, now.

22:36.355 --> 22:39.882
Got it.
Okay, let her go.

22:41.960 --> 22:43.128
Got her.

22:43.228 --> 22:45.264
Hey, Wes.
What the heck took you so long?

22:45.364 --> 22:48.066
Someone forgot to pave the damn road.

22:48.166 --> 22:51.966
Yeah, well, load 'em up.

22:52.838 --> 22:55.966
Okay, boss, whatever you say.

22:59.644 --> 23:04.064
Hey, that's the guy.
When l came up here with Amy...

23:04.249 --> 23:06.544
Hold her steady, would you?

23:09.388 --> 23:12.108
l got a really bad vibe off him.

23:12.958 --> 23:14.958
Come on.

23:16.027 --> 23:18.230
A whole lotta bull just to set 'em free again.

23:18.330 --> 23:22.410
Yeah, 60 cents a pound.
That's all they're worth.

23:24.603 --> 23:26.628
Go on.

23:35.814 --> 23:37.416
Okay, let it go.

23:37.516 --> 23:39.882
That's it, boy.

23:52.764 --> 23:54.764
Hey.

23:55.734 --> 23:57.734
What are you doing?

24:07.979 --> 24:10.449
Dammit, Jack.
What's your boy doing?

24:10.549 --> 24:12.813
Open that gate.

24:18.356 --> 24:20.092
Come on, man.

24:20.192 --> 24:22.319
That's enough, now.

24:22.494 --> 24:24.296
l said, enough.

24:24.396 --> 24:26.064
Get off me, old man.

24:26.164 --> 24:32.037
Your first punch better be good, son.
lt's the only one you're gonna get.

24:32.137 --> 24:34.137
Jack, you good?

24:34.573 --> 24:35.941
Yeah, l'm good.

24:36.041 --> 24:38.601
You better get Ty outta here.

24:38.710 --> 24:40.710
Ty, get in the truck.

24:46.651 --> 24:48.053
Don't even think about it.

24:48.153 --> 24:52.783
Wes. Let it go.

25:14.980 --> 25:17.955
l don't know what's wrong with him.

25:18.250 --> 25:21.583
Maybe he's a little stiff in his hocks.

25:23.889 --> 25:25.889
Uh, what are you doing?

25:26.791 --> 25:28.791
Going back to basics.

25:29.094 --> 25:32.030
What? Poles on the ground?
Funny, Nick.

25:32.130 --> 25:33.999
l want to see where the problem is,

25:34.099 --> 25:37.329
so bring Red to the base of the poles.

25:37.569 --> 25:39.371
You gotta be kidding me.

25:39.471 --> 25:40.439
No.

25:40.539 --> 25:43.875
Nick, what am l doing here, man,
pony rides?

25:43.975 --> 25:45.444
l'm trying to help you, man.

25:45.544 --> 25:48.349
l don't need your so-called help.

25:53.785 --> 25:55.720
Well, he may not be much of a jumper,

25:55.820 --> 25:59.722
but at least he can make an exit.

26:15.307 --> 26:18.538
lt's okay, boy, it's okay.

26:25.050 --> 26:29.316
lt's okay. lt's okay.

26:38.630 --> 26:40.996
Horses.

26:44.202 --> 26:47.296
Come on. lt's okay.

26:52.110 --> 26:54.679
Hey, l saw you talking to Nick.
What did you tell him?

26:54.779 --> 26:55.847
Nothing.

26:55.947 --> 27:00.197
Oh, yeah? Well, that nothing
screwed up everything.

27:00.885 --> 27:02.854
l wasn't gonna say anything,
but he kept asking.

27:02.954 --> 27:07.459
l'm paying him to be my coach,
and he's talking to you, like...

27:07.559 --> 27:08.793
When l was watching you,
l realized...

27:08.893 --> 27:10.462
...why you got so mad
when we moved your jumps.

27:10.562 --> 27:14.589
Yeah. My jumps. You moved them.
Big mystery.

27:14.733 --> 27:16.468
Look, you want to make
yourself feel good...

27:16.568 --> 27:18.403
...by going over a course
with no mistakes? Fine.

27:18.503 --> 27:19.905
That's the way l train, Amy.

27:20.005 --> 27:21.239
lt's not gonna do you any good.

27:21.339 --> 27:25.844
As soon as you get to a show,
the course is different.

27:26.845 --> 27:29.080
You know what the problem is anyway?

27:29.180 --> 27:31.883
l've been riding this horse
for three years now,

27:31.983 --> 27:33.485
and he's not getting any better.

27:33.585 --> 27:34.586
You're talking about Red?

27:34.686 --> 27:38.857
Yeah. Actually, you know what, Amy?
Maybe you did me a favor.

27:38.957 --> 27:41.693
'Cause l've maxed out on this horse.

27:41.793 --> 27:42.594
Give me your helmet.

27:42.694 --> 27:44.694
What are you doing?

27:49.200 --> 27:51.069
Put that jump up a couple of notches.

27:51.169 --> 27:51.570
What?

27:51.670 --> 27:53.271
Just do it.

27:53.371 --> 27:55.371
Yeah. Fine.

28:09.387 --> 28:11.387
That one too.

28:41.286 --> 28:45.484
There's nothing wrong with this horse.

29:09.047 --> 29:11.047
Come on.

29:15.186 --> 29:18.280
[ Horses neigh ]

29:41.546 --> 29:43.546
Horses?

29:43.581 --> 29:46.277
This is a feed lot.

29:52.490 --> 29:57.427
This is where they put cows
before they kill them.

30:13.178 --> 30:17.348
Yeah, and again, l'm so sorry
about the inconvenience.

30:17.448 --> 30:19.651
Oh, well, you know little girls
and their horses--

30:19.751 --> 30:22.020
Well, it's not actually her horse,

30:22.120 --> 30:25.156
but l'm sure in her mind
it's just a technicality.

30:25.256 --> 30:26.758
[ Cell phone rings ]

30:26.858 --> 30:28.326
Do you mind?

30:28.426 --> 30:30.426
Sorry.

30:30.862 --> 30:31.996
Mallory? Where are you?

30:32.096 --> 30:34.199
At the end of White Road.
Lou, there's all these horses.

30:34.299 --> 30:36.267
Slow down.
Tell me what's going on.

30:36.367 --> 30:37.702
You have to come.
Something bad's going on.

30:37.802 --> 30:42.796
l said, slow down.
- Just come. Just come. l mean it.

30:45.977 --> 30:48.146
LOU: l can't believe she ran away.

30:48.246 --> 30:49.514
l can't believe none of us noticed.

30:49.614 --> 30:51.249
l never said anything about re-homing.

30:51.349 --> 30:54.324
Well, you must have said something.

30:54.853 --> 30:57.655
l was talking to Mrs. Wiley,
telling her we had the perfect horse...

30:57.755 --> 31:00.087
...for a 1 2-year-old girl.

31:00.191 --> 31:05.376
Mallory was right there. She
must have thought l meant Copper.

31:13.304 --> 31:15.304
Anybody here?

31:15.607 --> 31:16.641
Ben.

31:16.741 --> 31:17.342
Hey.

31:17.442 --> 31:19.043
So? Where's Nick?

31:19.143 --> 31:22.881
Uh, he left.
Well, actually, l pulled the plug.

31:22.981 --> 31:25.506
You're kidding?
Look at you.

31:25.617 --> 31:28.286
Walking out of a clinic with Nick Harwell?

31:28.386 --> 31:29.454
Tell me all about it.

31:29.554 --> 31:33.358
There's nothing much to tell,
other than it really sucked.

31:33.458 --> 31:35.627
People pay thousands of dollars...

31:35.727 --> 31:37.595
Yeah. And that's why he is a total fraud.

31:37.695 --> 31:39.998
l mean, the guy has no idea
what he's doing.

31:40.098 --> 31:41.533
He actually asked Amy for advice.

31:41.633 --> 31:45.737
That's unbelievable.
l mean, l've seen you ride, Ben.

31:45.837 --> 31:47.038
lf you asked me for my advice,

31:47.138 --> 31:48.840
l'd say there's absolutely
nothing wrong with you.

31:48.940 --> 31:54.469
Maybe it's your horse.
Or your trainer. Or Amy Fleming.

31:55.079 --> 31:59.015
So, where is everybody?

32:00.051 --> 32:02.519
l don't know.

32:02.854 --> 32:05.049
We're alone?

32:05.223 --> 32:08.420
Yeah, l guess. Looks like it.

32:08.526 --> 32:11.763
You know, at night this pathetic
little barn doesn't look so bad.

32:11.863 --> 32:13.565
What are you talking about, Ash?

32:13.665 --> 32:14.933
Compared to the barns at Briar Ridge,

32:15.033 --> 32:18.008
this place is like, uh, a big shed.

32:18.236 --> 32:20.236
lt's kinda cosy.

32:21.572 --> 32:24.006
Ah, yeah, l guess.

32:24.876 --> 32:26.876
And romantic.

32:26.945 --> 32:28.945
l wouldn't go that far.

32:28.980 --> 32:30.980
l would.

32:37.188 --> 32:41.778
What took you guys so long?
l've been waiting for ever.

32:42.961 --> 32:45.864
This is crazy.
What are we doing here?

32:45.964 --> 32:49.874
Oh, my God. These horses
have no food or water.

32:50.068 --> 32:54.573
That's the stallion.
The one from up in the mountains.

32:55.707 --> 32:58.369
These are the Mustangs.

33:01.379 --> 33:05.083
Where the heck is everybody?
Nothing's been done.

33:05.183 --> 33:06.251
No feed. No water.

33:06.351 --> 33:08.953
Yeah, well, that's my job. lt's kinda
hard to do when you're not here.

33:09.053 --> 33:11.022
Would it kill somebody to pass a broom...

33:11.122 --> 33:12.290
...around here once in a while?

33:12.390 --> 33:14.225
lt's my job, Jack, okay?

33:14.325 --> 33:17.262
Maybe l made a mistake thinking
you might appreciate getting out,

33:17.362 --> 33:18.696
doing something a little different.

33:18.796 --> 33:21.733
Look, l appreciate it.
l'm sorry l wrecked your day, Jack.

33:21.833 --> 33:23.968
You might want to think about
working on that temper of yours too.

33:24.068 --> 33:27.538
My temper? l'm not the one
hitting that horse, Jack.

33:27.638 --> 33:29.474
Not your horse.
Not your problem.

33:29.574 --> 33:30.775
Yes, it is my problem.

33:30.875 --> 33:32.610
When someone's beating
on someone innocent,

33:32.710 --> 33:37.640
that makes it my problem,
and l'm not gonna put up with it.

33:40.918 --> 33:45.338
l have a feeling we're not talking
about horses here.

33:45.757 --> 33:49.427
Yeah, well, people like that
get what's coming to them.

33:49.527 --> 33:52.697
And you're just the guy
to give it to them, are you?

33:52.797 --> 33:54.432
Some kind of one man posse.

33:54.532 --> 33:56.501
Or a loose cannon
with impulse control issues.

33:56.601 --> 33:58.236
Depends which one of my
social workers you want to talk to.

33:58.336 --> 34:00.338
Well, do your social workers
cover your back too?

34:00.438 --> 34:04.876
'Cause let me tell you something,
that was strictly a one time deal.

34:04.976 --> 34:06.976
Jack...

34:07.011 --> 34:12.791
...l appreciate it. lt's not very often
people stick up for me. Okay?

34:14.385 --> 34:17.547
[ Phone rings ]

34:24.128 --> 34:24.862
Hello?

34:24.962 --> 34:27.264
Grandpa. You have to come quick.
Over at the end of Whites Road.

34:27.364 --> 34:30.001
We've found these Mustangs.
And it doesn't look good, okay?

34:30.101 --> 34:31.768
We're on our way.

34:31.869 --> 34:32.837
We gotta go.

34:32.937 --> 34:33.838
What's going on?

34:33.938 --> 34:36.063
l'll tell you on the way.

34:39.777 --> 34:42.313
l thought you said we were alone.

34:42.413 --> 34:47.646
Oh, man, l just said
what you wanted me to say.

34:47.752 --> 34:49.982
l like your attitude.

34:52.322 --> 34:53.558
[ Horses neigh ]

34:53.658 --> 34:56.860
Why would somebody
just dump these horses here?

34:56.960 --> 34:58.396
l've heard about this before.

34:58.496 --> 34:59.497
They're just gathering them here...

34:59.597 --> 35:01.065
...until they get enough
to make it worthwhile...

35:01.165 --> 35:02.500
...to ship them to the slaughterhouse.

35:02.600 --> 35:05.870
A slaughterhouse.
But you told me they were Mustangs.

35:05.970 --> 35:07.905
Yeah, exactly,
it just makes it easier.

35:08.005 --> 35:09.207
l mean, they are not owned by anyone.

35:09.307 --> 35:12.003
So they're impossible to trace.

35:12.110 --> 35:14.203
What's that?

35:22.320 --> 35:24.355
lt looks like a livestock trailer.

35:24.455 --> 35:25.623
Mallory, get in the truck.

35:25.723 --> 35:27.358
You're not going to let them
take them, are you?

35:27.458 --> 35:29.458
Now.

35:31.829 --> 35:33.831
Amy, maybe we should get in the truck too.

35:33.931 --> 35:35.233
There's not a lot we can do here.

35:35.333 --> 35:37.201
Get the gate.

35:37.301 --> 35:38.936
But all the horses will run away.

35:39.036 --> 35:41.205
That's the point.
Now, just get the gate.

35:41.305 --> 35:43.535
AMY: Come on. Come on.

35:44.675 --> 35:45.877
Come on, let's go.

35:45.977 --> 35:47.977
AMY: Come on, come on.

35:51.048 --> 35:51.849
l got it.

35:51.949 --> 35:53.949
Come on. Let's go.

35:56.921 --> 35:59.657
What's the matter?
Why aren't they leaving?

35:59.757 --> 36:02.902
Mallory.
Just turn off the headlights.

36:05.630 --> 36:07.098
Come on.

36:07.198 --> 36:09.530
Come on, let's go.

36:09.667 --> 36:12.472
Come on.
Come on, get out of here.

36:13.938 --> 36:15.239
Run.

36:15.339 --> 36:17.804
That's enough, Amy. Let's go.

36:30.388 --> 36:33.824
Amy. Look out.

36:38.129 --> 36:40.231
What the hell are you doing?

36:40.331 --> 36:41.999
Oh, look.
Ty's little girlfriend.

36:42.099 --> 36:44.302
These horses don't belong to you.

36:44.402 --> 36:46.402
Let her go.

36:48.306 --> 36:50.306
LOU: Leave her alone.

36:57.014 --> 36:59.014
Hey.

37:02.553 --> 37:04.553
Ty. Look out.

37:04.622 --> 37:06.622
Come here.

37:17.902 --> 37:18.836
Nobody move.

37:18.936 --> 37:21.606
Or the next one's got my name on it.

37:21.706 --> 37:24.732
Your name. Just don't move.

37:41.626 --> 37:43.961
You know, l can't believe
you lied to Mrs. Wiley.

37:44.061 --> 37:47.131
On the plus side,
she didn't believe it either.

37:47.231 --> 37:49.901
You actually thought
l was going to re-home Copper?

37:50.001 --> 37:53.771
He's your horse. You can do
whatever you want with him.

37:53.871 --> 37:55.640
Well, to tell you the truth,

37:55.740 --> 37:59.677
l have been thinking
about what we should do with him.

37:59.777 --> 38:02.113
And l'd might be willing to work out
a deal with you,

38:02.213 --> 38:04.213
based on sweat equity.

38:04.615 --> 38:06.517
l do enough sweating around here.

38:06.617 --> 38:11.462
This way, your sweat could be
an investment in the future.

38:11.589 --> 38:14.959
So, you're saying, l work my butt off,
like l already do,

38:15.059 --> 38:16.827
and in return...?

38:16.927 --> 38:19.392
We'd be equal partners.
50/50.

38:21.465 --> 38:25.460
So you couldn't re-home your 50%
without my 50%?

38:26.170 --> 38:28.720
Uh, yeah, something like that.

38:29.940 --> 38:31.175
Sweet.

38:31.275 --> 38:36.269
Which 50% is mine?
Heads or tails?

38:36.380 --> 38:37.281
Why don't we flip on it?

38:37.381 --> 38:40.818
No way. Knowing my luck,
l'll get the bum end of the deal.

38:40.918 --> 38:43.808
Hey, heads, l win.
Tails, you lose.

38:46.090 --> 38:49.685
Heads, l win.
Better start shoveling.

38:52.963 --> 38:56.296
And then Lou goes for the shotgun.

38:56.400 --> 39:00.004
Yeah, well, luckily l remembered
you keep one in your truck.

39:00.104 --> 39:02.470
Most ranchers do.

39:02.573 --> 39:04.041
Well, you really spooked those horses.

39:04.141 --> 39:06.877
l heard that a couple of them
made it halfway to Calgary...

39:06.977 --> 39:08.479
...before they were rounded up.

39:08.579 --> 39:10.945
Yeah, must have been,

39:11.082 --> 39:14.151
'Nobody moves or the next one's
got my name on it.'

39:14.251 --> 39:19.450
Or 'No, no, your name...'
Or somebody's name.

39:23.728 --> 39:28.032
You know, Lou, uh, l was thinking
of heading up to the mountains.

39:28.132 --> 39:30.132
You want to come along?

39:30.901 --> 39:32.901
What, now?

39:34.972 --> 39:39.392
l, uh, kinda had this other thing
l'm supposed to do.

39:42.246 --> 39:44.246
One time offer.

39:48.986 --> 39:53.320
l'll be waiting in the truck.
Oh, and dress warm.

40:10.541 --> 40:12.009
Hey, Nick.

40:12.109 --> 40:14.600
Yeah, it's Lou.

40:14.712 --> 40:17.948
You know what?
Actually, l can't make it today.

40:18.048 --> 40:23.953
Yeah. No, another time, l promise.
Okay, bye.

40:34.632 --> 40:36.200
Hey, Soraya.

40:36.300 --> 40:38.936
Hey. l didn't expect to see you here,
after last night.

40:39.036 --> 40:42.206
Everyone's talking about it.
You guys are total heroes.

40:42.306 --> 40:44.542
Yeah, well...
l have something to tell you.

40:44.642 --> 40:50.603
Um, last night, when we got home,
Ben had left. Red, his stuff.

40:50.714 --> 40:52.516
lt was all packed up and gone.

40:52.616 --> 40:54.709
l know.

40:54.819 --> 40:55.720
How?

40:55.820 --> 40:58.880
Um, Ashley.

40:58.989 --> 41:00.491
'Good news. Smiley face.

41:00.591 --> 41:03.327
Ben, heart, heart, heart, has left
the poverty barn, frowny face,

41:03.427 --> 41:05.262
and has gone back to Fairfield,
smiley face,

41:05.362 --> 41:09.697
so he can train with me,
heart, heart, smiley face.'

41:09.900 --> 41:11.369
l should have listened to you.

41:11.469 --> 41:13.537
And l'm glad that he's with Ashley...

41:13.637 --> 41:18.309
...because, you know, now she can
dump his ass and mess him up.

41:18.409 --> 41:20.478
At least she's good for something, right?

41:20.578 --> 41:22.578
'LOL.'

41:24.315 --> 41:25.416
The lab guy says...

41:25.516 --> 41:27.752
...the DNA matches up
with samples they have...

41:27.852 --> 41:29.553
...from old Spanish bloodlines.

41:29.653 --> 41:30.287
Wow.

41:30.387 --> 41:32.387
Amazing.

41:33.224 --> 41:35.860
So, uh, where are these Mustangs?

41:35.960 --> 41:37.061
This way, Lou.

41:37.161 --> 41:42.633
You don't expect them to be standing
on the side of the road, do you?

41:42.733 --> 41:45.429
Oh, come on, Scott.

41:45.536 --> 41:51.146
Well, the road doesn't go past here.
And it's quite a trek on foot.

41:54.478 --> 41:56.742
Come on, boy.

41:57.014 --> 42:00.074
Oh, what the hell.

42:07.658 --> 42:09.658
Hey, Ty.

42:12.229 --> 42:15.289
l, ah, heard about what happened.

42:15.399 --> 42:20.538
l should've known that guy was
bad news from the day he signed on.

42:20.638 --> 42:22.106
Hi, Amy.

42:22.206 --> 42:23.841
Hi, Dad.

42:23.941 --> 42:29.607
l was just telling Ty here
that l, well, l fired that guy... Wes.

42:30.114 --> 42:31.081
He didn't take it too good.

42:31.181 --> 42:33.184
Figure that's the least of his problems.

42:33.284 --> 42:34.618
Jack called the cops on him.

42:34.718 --> 42:40.158
Well, l don't know if he broke
any laws, but he's on their radar.

42:41.559 --> 42:42.827
So l was wondering...

42:42.927 --> 42:46.130
...if you might have some time
for your old man this week?

42:46.230 --> 42:48.960
Um, l'm kind of busy.

42:49.533 --> 42:51.533
Ah.

42:54.672 --> 42:58.497
Maybe you could come out
to the ranch, though.

43:00.210 --> 43:02.210
Saturday?

43:04.048 --> 43:06.642
Okay.

43:07.785 --> 43:10.379
l'll see you Saturday.

43:10.487 --> 43:12.487
At the ranch.

43:12.856 --> 43:14.856
Yeah, yeah.

43:29.707 --> 43:31.475
You're still pretty good on a horse.

43:31.575 --> 43:34.778
A guy l once knew said it was
just like riding a bicycle.

43:34.878 --> 43:36.580
You never forget?

43:36.680 --> 43:39.400
Unfortunately.
That's my problem.

43:40.184 --> 43:42.311
Oh, look right there.

43:52.296 --> 43:54.296
Hey...

43:59.370 --> 44:01.429
Thank you.

44:01.705 --> 44:03.705
For everything.

